'''Comedy thrillers''' are a [[cross-genre]] that draw subject matter generally from [[comedy]] and [[Thriller (genre)|thrillers]]. They often include a darker tone, relative to other genres, of humor. Just like regular thrillers, they often involve either [[organized crime]] or [[espionage]].
Examples of comedy thrillers in films, plays and novels are ''[[Charade (1963 film)|Charade]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9A0DE6DA1E30EF3BBC4E53DFB4678388679EDE|title = Screen: Audrey Hepburn and Grant in 'Charade':Comedy-Melodrama Is at the Music Hall Production Abounds in Ghoulish Humor|last = Crowther|first = Bosley|date = December 6, 1963|website = The New York Times|series = Movies|access-date = April 20, 2016}}</ref> ''[[The Thin Man (film)|The Thin Man]]'', ''[[The Lady Vanishes (1938 film)|The Lady Vanishes]]'', ''[[In Bruges]]'', ''[[Silver Streak (film)|Silver Streak]]'', ''[[Mr. and Mrs. Smith (2005 film)|Mr. and Mrs. Smith]]'', ''[[No Way to Treat a Lady (film)|No Way to Treat a Lady]]'', ''[[Kiss Kiss Bang Bang]]'', ''[[Kshana Kshanam]]'', ''[[The Big Fix (1978 film)|The Big Fix]]'', ''[[Lucky Number Slevin]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://www.nytimes.com/2006/03/23/nyregion/23bold.html|title = At a Screening of a Comedy Thriller About Revenge|last = Robertson|first = Campbell|date = March 23, 2006|website = The New York Times|series = New York / Region|access-date = April 20, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Deathtrap (film)|Deathtrap]]'', ''[[The Ladykillers]]'', ''[[Hopscotch (film)|Hopscotch]]'', ''[[Welcome to Collinwood]]'', ''[[The King of Comedy (film)|The King of Comedy]]''<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/03/28/a-restored-king-of-comedy-will-close-tribeca-film-festival/|title = A Restored ‘King of Comedy’ Will Close Tribeca Film Festival|last = Itzkoff|first = Dave|date = March 28, 2013|website = The New York Times|series = ArtsBeat|access-date = April 20, 2016}}</ref> and ''[[A Simple Favor (film)|A Simple Favor]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/paul-feig-aimed-revive-hitchcockian-thriller-a-simple-favor-1142803|title=Why Paul Feig Aimed to Revive the "Hitchcockian Thriller" With 'A Simple Favor'|publisher=}}</ref>
